column1:
Gross enrolment ratio, primary (% of primary school-age population)
SDG 4.1 By 2030, ensure that all girls and boys complete free, equitable and quality primary and secondary education leading to relevant and effective learning outcomes
Dimension: Education
Definition: Total enrolment in a given level of education (pre-primary, primary, secondary or tertiary), regardless of age, expressed as a percentage of the official school-age population for the same level of education.
Source: UNESCO (United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) Institute for Statistics (2019). Data Centre. http://data.uis.unesco.org. Accessed 11 April 2019.

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development

column1: a: Data refer to the most recent year available during the period specified.
